GENERATION 1: THE FOUNDERS — Speedwell 4 July 1752
Pierre Boutilier (1720–1796) — Your 6x Great-Grandfather

Born: Montbéliard, France. French Protestant / Huguenot.
Arrived: Halifax 4 July 1752 on ship Speedwell with wife Marguerite Tanner + 3 children.
Settled: Boutilier’s Point, St. Margaret’s Bay. Founder of the Boutilier families of NS.
Died: 1796. Buried St. Paul’s Anglican Cemetery, French Village.
Jean Dauphinee (1722–1798) — Your 6x Great-Grandfather

Born: Montbéliard, France. Huguenot.
Arrived: Same ship Speedwell 1752 with wife Marie Madeleine Mourand + 2 children.
Settled: Hacketts Cove, St. Margaret’s Bay.
Died: 1798. Buried St. Paul’s Anglican Cemetery.
Result: You descend from two original 1752 Foreign Protestant families.

